benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/export/{accountId} - Export account data

covered: Valid Request: 200 OK with application/octet-stream and a valid account export is asserted.
Required/optional headers: X-Killbill-CreatedBy enforced (400 when missing); X-Killbill-Reason and X-Killbill-Comment optional and accepted.
Path parameter validation: accountId UUID format enforced; malformed and injection inputs return 400.
Not-found handling: 404 returned when the account does not exist or when the DB is empty.
Authorization: 401 for missing/invalid auth token is covered (if authentication is required).
Resiliency/performance: large export handling, slow downstream (still 200), service unavailable (500), and timeout (504) are covered.
Negative robustness: extra/unsupported headers tolerated, unsupported HTTP method returns 405, missing path variable returns 404.
Regression/backward compatibility/accessibility: Content-Type regression verified; legacy header tolerated; documentation accessibility checked.
Non-applicable acknowledged: Pagination and query parameters do not apply to this single-resource export and are excluded from coverage.
gaps: Empty Response: Behavior when an existing account has no exportable data (200 with minimal archive vs 204 No Content) is not defined or tested.
Authorization depth: No scenario for 403 Forbidden (valid auth but insufficient permissions/role).
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling/429 responses or Retry-After headers under burst traffic.
Caching Behavior: No validation of Cache-Control policy (e.g., no-store) and absence/presence of validators (ETag/Last-Modified) or conditional GET behavior.
Export artifact validation: Tests do not verify the octet-stream is a decompressible archive with expected files/content mapped to the account.
Error contract: Error payload/schema and Content-Type for 4xx/5xx responses are not asserted (e.g., standard Kill Bill error fields).
Content-Disposition/filename: No assertion that downloads are served as attachment with a sensible, deterministic filename.
recommendations: Define and test behavior when an account exists but has no exportable records; add a scenario for either 200 with a minimal archive or 204 No Content, per API spec.
Add a 403 Forbidden scenario using a valid token lacking the required scope/role.
Introduce rate-limiting scenarios: generate bursts to trigger 429; assert Retry-After and any rate-limit headers.

Add caching checks: assert Cache-Control policy (e.g., no-store or private); validate ETag/Last-Modified if used; exercise conditional GET with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since expecting 304 if unchanged.
Strengthen export validation by downloading the stream, verifying it is decompressible, and asserting expected files/records for a known seeded account.
Assert standardized error responses across 400/404/500/504: structure, fields, and Content-Type; include correlation/request id headers if applicable.
Assert Content-Disposition header (attachment; filename=<accountId>-export.zip or similar) and verify consistent filename pattern across requests.
